Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dedric Demond Vaughns Jr not in court, in custody.  
Attorney Colleen A Taylor in court for Dedric Demond Vaughns Jr.  
Attorney Erika Strebel for Stephan Eduard Nolten in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a Status Conference.  Defense request a resolution date.   
Defense advised plea documents to be submitted to the court 24-hours in advance of the hearing. 
Court ordered matter adjourned back to Branch 19.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 16, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Attorney Colleen A Taylor in court, defendant Dedric Demond Vaughns not in court, in custody on a revocation hold.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for Stephan Nolten the State of Wisconsin.  State informed the court that the case is mis-tabbed and should be properly assigned to Branch 45.   Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 45.   Pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-04, parties are hereby notified that as of July 30, 2022, this case will be assigned to Branch 19, Judge Kori Ashley, in Room 313 of the Safety Building.  Status conference scheduled for September 6, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Dedric Demond Vaughns in court with Attorney Colleen A Taylor.  Defendant Dedric Demond Vaughns in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer N. Sandoval. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Judge Franke.  Scheduling conference scheduled for July 22, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Dedric Demond Vaughns in court with Attorney Colleen A Taylor; both appear by video.  Defendant Dedric Demond Vaughns in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness was present. Due to court congestion court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 29, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Dedric Demond Vaughns in court with attorney Colleen A Taylor.  Defendant Dedric Demond Vaughns in custody.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Dedric Demond Vaughns appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Sanders, Branch 28. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 2, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
